1
00:00:18,601 --> 00:00:19,978
Go out with me.

2
00:00:24,107 --> 00:00:25,734
And I'll tell you everything.

3
00:00:26,818 --> 00:00:28,695
- (Yeo Saebyeok.)
- (Yes?)

4
00:00:29,612 --> 00:00:30,530
(Do you like me?)

5
00:00:32,832 --> 00:00:33,632
I love you.

6
00:00:41,958 --> 00:00:43,168
Okay?

7
00:01:02,848 --> 00:01:04,230
Are you crazy, Gi Haneul?

8
00:01:04,544 --> 00:01:06,316
Come on. Let's go on a date.

9
00:01:06,316 --> 00:01:07,776
I'm not going. Let go.

10
00:01:07,776 --> 00:01:10,780
A WeTV ORIGINAL SERIES

11
00:01:13,740 --> 00:01:15,900
GI HANEUL
HWANG JUNSU

12
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:20,620
IN ASSOCIATION WITH YYDS

13
00:01:22,160 --> 00:01:25,120
YEO SAEBYEOK
LEE JAWOON

14
00:01:31,590 --> 00:01:34,340
YOON JUNGHAN
OH JAEHYEONG

15
00:01:35,340 --> 00:01:37,550
LEE SERI
PARK EUNJO

16
00:01:42,602 --> 00:01:49,275
=Never Forget Your Enemy=

17
00:01:51,277 --> 00:01:55,573
=Episode 3=
(I Love You)

18
00:02:02,956 --> 00:02:04,457
Where are we going?

19
00:02:04,707 --> 00:02:06,167
Just walk 30 more minutes.

20
00:02:06,376 --> 00:02:07,293
This is crazy.

21
00:02:07,627 --> 00:02:08,294
Hey.

22
00:02:09,129 --> 00:02:10,797
Another 30 minutes from here?

23
00:02:11,422 --> 00:02:12,768
We'll run into wild boars.

24
00:02:12,768 --> 00:02:13,856
No wild boars here.

25
00:02:14,092 --> 00:02:15,456
But there'll be other animals.

26
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:18,464
Hmm?

27
00:02:20,390 --> 00:02:21,141
There is.

28
00:02:22,267 --> 00:02:23,059
What?

29
00:02:24,561 --> 00:02:25,478
Behind you.

30
00:02:26,479 --> 00:02:27,730
What?

31
00:02:27,772 --> 00:02:28,648
What is it?

32
00:02:35,446 --> 00:02:36,531
Do you want to die?

33
00:02:37,031 --> 00:02:38,491
Do you want to die here?

34
00:02:38,867 --> 00:02:39,534
Ah?

35
00:02:39,784 --> 00:02:40,618
Want me to help you?

36
00:02:41,286 --> 00:02:42,120
Not a bad idea.

37
00:02:42,287 --> 00:02:44,038
I could be with you forever.

38
00:02:44,622 --> 00:02:46,291
You've never changed,

39
00:02:46,666 --> 00:02:47,625
acting like a schoolboy.

40
00:02:48,168 --> 00:02:49,856
The sincerity
of a schoolboy is like this.

41
00:02:49,856 --> 00:02:50,545
Come on.

42
00:03:01,598 --> 00:03:02,223
Almost there.

43
00:03:03,349 --> 00:03:04,726
Didn't you say 30 more minutes?

44
00:03:05,393 --> 00:03:06,269
Is this the place?

45
00:03:06,436 --> 00:03:09,397
We arrived earlier than expected.
It makes you feel good, right?

46
00:03:11,482 --> 00:03:12,442
Come on.

47
00:03:13,151 --> 00:03:13,985
Take a look.

48
00:03:23,744 --> 00:03:25,038
It's so beautiful.

49
00:03:28,958 --> 00:03:30,877
But where is this?

50
00:03:33,004 --> 00:03:34,839
A place
of great historical significance.

51
00:03:36,382 --> 00:03:37,467
Why are we here?

52
00:03:38,301 --> 00:03:41,137
Do you know why the Imjin War happened?

53
00:03:42,639 --> 00:03:43,389
Why?

54
00:03:46,496 --> 00:03:47,424
Because of negligence.

55
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:52,982
I won't announce your death.

56
00:03:54,901 --> 00:03:57,028
You're dead.

57
00:03:59,530 --> 00:04:00,949
You don't remember this place?

58
00:04:01,115 --> 00:04:01,615
I don't.

59
00:04:01,699 --> 00:04:02,199
I don't.

60
00:04:03,284 --> 00:04:05,411
There's no way
you don't remember this place.

61
00:04:05,536 --> 00:04:06,955
You said you liked doing it here.

62
00:04:07,664 --> 00:04:08,206
It's dark.

63
00:04:08,498 --> 00:04:09,582
Nobody around.

64
00:04:09,666 --> 00:04:10,333
Wide open.

65
00:04:12,210 --> 00:04:12,710
What?

66
00:04:12,752 --> 00:04:13,252
Doing what?

67
00:04:14,921 --> 00:04:15,797
I don't like it.

68
00:04:16,798 --> 00:04:17,382
Don't you?

69
00:04:17,799 --> 00:04:18,299
No, I don't.

70
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:20,301
Really?

71
00:04:20,635 --> 00:04:22,428
So let's come back when you remember.

72
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:29,102
I'll do it properly then.

73
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:31,312
Hey, you...

74
00:04:31,354 --> 00:04:34,190
You leave, what do I do?
Let's go together!

75
00:04:46,661 --> 00:04:47,870
Excuse me.

76
00:04:48,037 --> 00:04:50,999
You look so much like him.
Are you Yeo Saebyeok?

77
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:51,541
Yes, I am.

78
00:04:53,584 --> 00:04:55,211
Can I have your autograph?

79
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:55,795
Sure.

80
00:04:56,087 --> 00:04:57,130
Thank you.

81
00:04:58,381 --> 00:04:59,382
What's your name?

82
00:04:59,590 --> 00:05:00,842
I'm Chaehee.

83
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:06,180
- Thanks.
- Thanks.

84
00:05:14,272 --> 00:05:15,773
So you really are a star?

85
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:17,692
Want my autograph?

86
00:05:21,487 --> 00:05:23,656
How did such a bad guy
like you become a star?

87
00:05:25,491 --> 00:05:26,743
Bad boys are charming.

88
00:05:27,618 --> 00:05:28,661
Crazy.

89
00:05:34,083 --> 00:05:35,543
Why are you mad again?

90
00:05:39,839 --> 00:05:40,965
Because I envy you.

91
00:05:50,767 --> 00:05:52,268
Gi Haneul, are you okay?

92
00:05:52,602 --> 00:05:53,394
Does it hurt a lot?

93
00:05:57,774 --> 00:05:58,900
I'm fine.

94
00:06:00,068 --> 00:06:00,985
It doesn't hurt much.

95
00:06:01,408 --> 00:06:03,905
You're coming off an injury.
I shouldn't have brought you out.

96
00:06:03,905 --> 00:06:05,490
Let's go to the hospital. Wait for me.

97
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:06,657
I said I'm fine.

98
00:06:08,493 --> 00:06:09,243
Haneul.

99
00:06:10,620 --> 00:06:11,871
I said I'm fine. Let's go home.

100
00:06:12,580 --> 00:06:14,582
What if something's wrong?

101
00:06:15,541 --> 00:06:17,335
What more could be wrong with me?

102
00:06:20,838 --> 00:06:21,881
I want to go home.

103
00:06:24,384 --> 00:06:26,177
Wait, I'll go get the car.

104
00:06:37,105 --> 00:06:38,356
(In front of the school.)

105
00:06:39,732 --> 00:06:41,609
(We have to talk in person.)

106
00:06:49,274 --> 00:06:51,202
(Emergency Center)

107
00:06:51,202 --> 00:06:53,454
Wake up, Haneul.

108
00:06:53,454 --> 00:06:56,958
Gi Haneul, open your eyes.

109
00:06:58,084 --> 00:07:01,629
Mom and Saetbyeol are here.
Do you see us, Haneul?

110
00:07:06,134 --> 00:07:09,095
(I have something to say to you.)

111
00:07:09,762 --> 00:07:10,430
(Gi Haneul.)

112
00:07:10,930 --> 00:07:11,931
Just listen to me.

113
00:07:12,432 --> 00:07:13,391
Listen to what?

114
00:07:13,696 --> 00:07:15,200
Did you come here just to say that?

115
00:07:18,104 --> 00:07:18,771
You murderer.

116
00:07:26,821 --> 00:07:29,282
Are you okay? Let's go to the hospital.

117
00:07:38,624 --> 00:07:40,793
Gi Haneul, wait for me.

118
00:07:50,656 --> 00:07:51,552
Gi Haneul.

119
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,024
What's wrong with you?

120
00:07:53,024 --> 00:07:54,307
None of your business.

121
00:07:56,032 --> 00:07:57,268
How can I not care?

122
00:07:59,232 --> 00:08:00,256
Who do you think you are?

123
00:08:02,080 --> 00:08:03,024
It will all pass.

124
00:08:04,233 --> 00:08:04,928
Is that so?

125
00:08:06,152 --> 00:08:07,392
Then tell me.

126
00:08:07,968 --> 00:08:09,248
What will happen to me?

127
00:08:10,016 --> 00:08:11,552
I know you're confused.

128
00:08:11,552 --> 00:08:12,742
But it's not a big deal.

129
00:08:16,544 --> 00:08:18,528
My life isn't a big deal?

130
00:08:20,352 --> 00:08:21,626
Easy for you to say.

131
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:25,440
None of this is your fault.

132
00:08:27,673 --> 00:08:28,508
What?

133
00:08:29,248 --> 00:08:30,400
What makes you say that?

134
00:08:31,385 --> 00:08:32,136
How ridiculous.

135
00:08:32,178 --> 00:08:33,179
Can't I say that?

136
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:33,971
No, you can't.

137
00:08:34,430 --> 00:08:35,431
Who do you think you are?

138
00:08:35,648 --> 00:08:38,184
You think because you're a star,
you can pity me?

139
00:08:38,880 --> 00:08:41,187
And you even tricked a cripple
into living with you.

140
00:08:41,187 --> 00:08:43,328
Are you helping the disadvantaged?

141
00:08:44,482 --> 00:08:45,888
Feeling pretty accomplished, huh?

142
00:08:46,817 --> 00:08:47,488
Mind your words.

143
00:08:48,064 --> 00:08:48,736
Sorry.

144
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:50,368
I'm petty.

145
00:08:51,552 --> 00:08:53,449
Seeing others do well
makes me insanely jealous.

146
00:08:53,792 --> 00:08:54,944
So I'm being unreasonable.

147
00:08:55,936 --> 00:08:56,704
My apologies.

148
00:08:56,704 --> 00:08:57,568
What's wrong?

149
00:08:57,568 --> 00:08:58,720
I just can't figure it out!

150
00:08:58,720 --> 00:09:00,873
I can't understand all the way through!

151
00:09:01,376 --> 00:09:02,833
Honestly, if you were me, could you?

152
00:09:03,072 --> 00:09:04,669
I'm 29 years old now,

153
00:09:04,669 --> 00:09:05,920
in a relationship with you.

154
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:07,264
And my leg is injured.

155
00:09:08,096 --> 00:09:10,341
I can't understand any of this.
What am I supposed to do?

156
00:09:10,341 --> 00:09:11,744
Have you tried to figure it out?

157
00:09:11,744 --> 00:09:13,120
Haven't you been avoiding it?

158
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:14,011
You know nothing.

159
00:09:14,011 --> 00:09:16,097
Then tell me
what you've been doing all this time.

160
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:17,728
Have you tried to jog your memory?

161
00:09:17,728 --> 00:09:19,616
Have you ever asked
what kind of person you are?

162
00:09:19,616 --> 00:09:21,644
Or how you lived?

163
00:09:21,644 --> 00:09:24,146
I don't know where to start.
How am I supposed to ask?

164
00:09:24,512 --> 00:09:25,648
If I tell you everything,

165
00:09:25,952 --> 00:09:27,358
will you have the nerve to hear it?

166
00:09:28,692 --> 00:09:29,652
I don't want to hear it.

167
00:09:29,652 --> 00:09:31,168
Then what exactly do you want?

168
00:09:31,168 --> 00:09:32,613
You just need me out of your sight?

169
00:09:32,613 --> 00:09:33,322
Yes!

170
00:09:33,536 --> 00:09:34,656
If possible, just go away.

171
00:09:34,656 --> 00:09:35,616
Gi Haneul.

172
00:09:46,816 --> 00:09:47,795
(You...)

173
00:09:48,462 --> 00:09:50,339
Haneul, are you okay?

174
00:09:50,339 --> 00:09:52,258
(You never believed in me.)

175
00:09:52,608 --> 00:09:54,552
(It's all my fault.)

176
00:09:55,488 --> 00:09:57,760
- (I never expected that!)
- Just go to the hospital.

177
00:10:28,768 --> 00:10:30,171
It's very late.

178
00:10:30,496 --> 00:10:31,756
Get some more sleep.

179
00:10:34,944 --> 00:10:36,736
Did it happen to my leg before?

180
00:10:36,736 --> 00:10:39,305
Occasionally,
when you're stressed or feeling unwell.

181
00:10:40,416 --> 00:10:42,350
It hasn't happened recently.

182
00:10:43,232 --> 00:10:45,102
It's hardly ever been a problem.

183
00:10:46,015 --> 00:10:46,730
I'm sorry.

184
00:10:52,096 --> 00:10:54,445
I shouldn't have yelled at you earlier.

185
00:10:55,776 --> 00:10:56,739
Hmm.

186
00:10:59,616 --> 00:11:02,244
If I knew it would turn out like this,

187
00:11:03,584 --> 00:11:05,081
I shouldn't have trained so hard.

188
00:11:06,656 --> 00:11:09,312
You looked cool
when you tried your best.

189
00:11:09,952 --> 00:11:11,462
Not cool now, right?

190
00:11:12,576 --> 00:11:13,798
Now, you're cute.

191
00:11:15,424 --> 00:11:16,416
That's cheesy.

192
00:11:19,584 --> 00:11:22,306
You always stand up for others.

193
00:11:22,656 --> 00:11:24,225
You cared about me when I was lonely.

194
00:11:25,664 --> 00:11:28,187
Even when facing setbacks,
you never gave up.

195
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:30,481
You are brave,

196
00:11:30,481 --> 00:11:31,649
warm,

197
00:11:32,032 --> 00:11:33,317
and strong.

198
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:35,444
So,

199
00:11:36,288 --> 00:11:37,780
don't give up this time either.

200
00:11:42,784 --> 00:11:43,808
Move it.

201
00:11:50,432 --> 00:11:51,877
Is there anything to eat at home?

202
00:11:53,696 --> 00:11:54,720
Let go.

203
00:11:55,104 --> 00:11:56,006
I'll cook.

204
00:11:56,064 --> 00:11:56,965
Hey.

205
00:11:57,120 --> 00:11:59,232
My leg is injured,
but my hands are fine.

206
00:11:59,776 --> 00:12:00,480
Let go.

207
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:01,952
Let me cook.

208
00:12:01,952 --> 00:12:03,680
Why are you like this?

209
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:05,472
Did you hide something there?

210
00:12:05,472 --> 00:12:06,517
What is it? Give it to me.

211
00:12:07,351 --> 00:12:08,102
You

212
00:12:08,928 --> 00:12:10,080
can't cook ramen.

213
00:12:11,264 --> 00:12:13,232
I have the strength to cook ramen.

214
00:12:14,336 --> 00:12:15,568
That's not what I meant.

215
00:12:15,776 --> 00:12:16,526
Then what?

216
00:12:17,472 --> 00:12:18,976
The ramen you cook

217
00:12:19,808 --> 00:12:20,865
doesn't taste good.

218
00:12:29,123 --> 00:12:31,834
You actually finished it all?

219
00:12:32,416 --> 00:12:33,919
It was actually pretty good.

220
00:12:47,296 --> 00:12:48,934
Which one is your room?

221
00:12:49,632 --> 00:12:50,728
That one.

222
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:54,190
Isn't that my room?

223
00:12:54,976 --> 00:12:55,808
Not your room.

224
00:12:55,808 --> 00:12:56,736
It's a master bedroom.

225
00:12:59,008 --> 00:13:00,544
What are you trying to say now?

226
00:13:01,088 --> 00:13:02,740
Don't you know what a master bedroom is?

227
00:13:02,740 --> 00:13:03,968
It's for couples.

228
00:13:03,968 --> 00:13:05,952
It's the room where we sleep together.

229
00:13:05,952 --> 00:13:07,424
C-Couples?

230
00:13:08,352 --> 00:13:09,538
What nonsense!

231
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:11,680
Is there any reason to sleep separately?

232
00:13:11,680 --> 00:13:12,800
No reason to sleep together.

233
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:14,016
It's been seven years.

234
00:13:14,016 --> 00:13:17,171
After living together for seven years,
isn't it weirder to sleep separately?

235
00:13:17,464 --> 00:13:18,784
Boundaries between men and women.

236
00:13:18,784 --> 00:13:19,712
But we're both men.

237
00:13:19,712 --> 00:13:20,716
Even more boundaries.

238
00:13:22,048 --> 00:13:23,344
Want me to share a bed with you?

239
00:13:23,968 --> 00:13:24,768
No way.

240
00:13:26,656 --> 00:13:28,432
Stop talking nonsense.

241
00:13:28,672 --> 00:13:29,792
Starting today,

242
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:32,800
this is my room.

243
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:34,784
That one is your room.

244
00:13:36,672 --> 00:13:37,440
No way.

245
00:13:38,016 --> 00:13:39,328
I'm a patient.

246
00:13:39,328 --> 00:13:41,440
If you sneak into my room,
I'll run away from home.

247
00:13:42,016 --> 00:13:42,816
Remember it.

248
00:13:43,336 --> 00:13:44,096
I go off to sleep.

249
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:47,993
Do dishes before going to bed.

250
00:14:11,232 --> 00:14:12,608
He's actually hustling hard.

251
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:15,396
(Have you tried to jog your memory?)

252
00:14:15,396 --> 00:14:17,280
Have you ever asked
what kind of person you are?

253
00:14:17,280 --> 00:14:19,232
Or how you lived?

254
00:14:19,584 --> 00:14:20,734
That arrogant guy.

255
00:14:21,952 --> 00:14:23,584
I have my own considerations too.

256
00:14:31,872 --> 00:14:32,997
Hey, Mom.

257
00:14:33,792 --> 00:14:35,666
I'm heading to Saetbyeol's coffee shop.

258
00:14:39,040 --> 00:14:41,839
What? I'll be home tomorrow.

259
00:14:48,064 --> 00:14:49,216
Ah, Haneul.

260
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:50,752
Told you to call in advance.

261
00:14:50,752 --> 00:14:51,807
I forgot.

262
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:54,393
Today is the first day.

263
00:14:55,072 --> 00:14:56,061
What?

264
00:14:56,061 --> 00:14:57,396
Your first day on the job.

265
00:14:57,824 --> 00:14:59,148
What were you thinking about?

266
00:14:59,148 --> 00:15:00,024
What?

267
00:15:00,024 --> 00:15:00,800
What do you mean?

268
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:02,144
I wasn't thinking about anything.

269
00:15:03,136 --> 00:15:05,440
You look definitely cuter
than when you're crying.

270
00:15:06,560 --> 00:15:07,656
When did I cry?

271
00:15:08,160 --> 00:15:10,656
People with this kind of face
tend to be a bit of a crybaby.

272
00:15:10,656 --> 00:15:11,872
Oh, please.

273
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:14,079
You look like a big crybaby.

274
00:15:17,536 --> 00:15:18,656
How do you know?

275
00:15:20,192 --> 00:15:21,856
Then cry out loud, cry with pride.

276
00:15:21,856 --> 00:15:23,005
Holding it back is not good.

277
00:15:23,968 --> 00:15:25,424
I wonder if you heard of something,

278
00:15:26,112 --> 00:15:28,416
or if you just said so unintentionally.

279
00:15:29,088 --> 00:15:30,688
Stop mumbling and get to work.

280
00:15:32,224 --> 00:15:33,223
Haneul.

281
00:15:33,952 --> 00:15:35,726
You really don't remember what happened?

282
00:15:36,288 --> 00:15:36,992
On the road?

283
00:15:38,896 --> 00:15:39,980
Are you kidding again?

284
00:15:43,936 --> 00:15:44,818
Sure.

285
00:15:45,888 --> 00:15:47,040
Go get changed.

286
00:15:53,440 --> 00:15:56,330
Too many coffee beans make it bitter,
but too few make it weak.

287
00:15:56,956 --> 00:15:57,790
I see.

288
00:15:58,207 --> 00:15:59,917
I never noticed
when I was just drinking.

289
00:16:01,984 --> 00:16:03,504
Try it now.

290
00:16:10,208 --> 00:16:12,805
This is the one you made.
This is the one I just made.

291
00:16:13,514 --> 00:16:14,144
Taste them.

292
00:16:26,592 --> 00:16:28,288
They taste completely different.

293
00:16:29,738 --> 00:16:31,949
The one you made is a bit sour.

294
00:16:32,608 --> 00:16:34,159
Why does the one I made

295
00:16:34,688 --> 00:16:36,078
have a burnt flavor?

296
00:16:36,448 --> 00:16:38,831
Just now,
the machine pressure was different.

297
00:16:39,584 --> 00:16:42,418
Though it looks simple,
a small difference changes the taste.

298
00:16:43,264 --> 00:16:45,045
Nothing is easy.

299
00:16:45,504 --> 00:16:47,423
Sports seem easier.

300
00:16:49,120 --> 00:16:50,259
Tennis,

301
00:16:50,259 --> 00:16:51,593
do you want to play again?

302
00:16:53,792 --> 00:16:54,429
Play it again?

303
00:16:55,040 --> 00:16:56,473
I don't want to, anyway.

304
00:16:57,664 --> 00:16:58,433
Why?

305
00:16:58,433 --> 00:16:59,727
Because it's tiring.

306
00:17:00,288 --> 00:17:02,104
I also hate the smell of boys' sweat.

307
00:17:02,304 --> 00:17:03,939
Summer is really unbearable, isn't it?

308
00:17:03,939 --> 00:17:04,690
Exactly.

309
00:17:04,888 --> 00:17:06,528
There's always someone
who doesn't shower.

310
00:17:06,528 --> 00:17:09,486
They even say
they're the type who doesn't sweat.

311
00:17:09,486 --> 00:17:11,071
Does that even make sense?

312
00:17:11,071 --> 00:17:12,573
Their clothes are clearly soaked.

313
00:17:13,152 --> 00:17:14,074
So gross.

314
00:17:17,327 --> 00:17:18,579
- Welcome.
- Welcome.

315
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:20,800
(Summer Crush)

316
00:17:20,800 --> 00:17:23,584
It's time we aimed for bigger stages.

317
00:17:23,904 --> 00:17:25,252
(Jang Jinhui)
Let's head to Hollywood!

318
00:17:25,984 --> 00:17:29,214
Director Elliot Jung
is starting a new film.

319
00:17:29,472 --> 00:17:31,592
He contacted us,

320
00:17:31,776 --> 00:17:33,218
asking to work with you.

321
00:17:33,664 --> 00:17:37,014
He said the lead must be Yeo Saebyeok.

322
00:17:37,696 --> 00:17:38,557
Saebyeok,

323
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:40,434
we've finally made it

324
00:17:40,896 --> 00:17:42,688
after all the hardship.

325
00:17:43,072 --> 00:17:43,808
Mr. Jang.

326
00:17:44,896 --> 00:17:46,899
After you wrap up the drama
you're filming,

327
00:17:46,899 --> 00:17:48,128
we'll fly straight to America

328
00:17:48,128 --> 00:17:49,777
to meet the director
and start preparing.

329
00:17:49,856 --> 00:17:51,616
Mr. Jang, I need to say something.

330
00:17:51,616 --> 00:17:52,738
What is it?

331
00:17:53,056 --> 00:17:54,114
Go ahead.

332
00:17:54,464 --> 00:17:56,608
Whatever you say, I'll agree.

333
00:17:56,608 --> 00:17:57,792
I can't go to America.

334
00:17:57,792 --> 00:17:59,411
Okay, you can't go.

335
00:18:00,608 --> 00:18:01,580
What?

336
00:18:02,624 --> 00:18:03,540
You can't go?

337
00:18:03,808 --> 00:18:04,499
Hey.

338
00:18:04,768 --> 00:18:05,632
Are you kidding?

339
00:18:05,632 --> 00:18:08,064
Haneul is sick. I need to be with him.

340
00:18:09,664 --> 00:18:10,432
Hey!

341
00:18:10,880 --> 00:18:12,576
Do you know what chance is this?

342
00:18:12,832 --> 00:18:15,424
Are you giving up Hollywood for a guy?

343
00:18:16,320 --> 00:18:18,013
Haneul is the most important to me.

344
00:18:18,013 --> 00:18:19,200
Yeo Saebyeok!

345
00:18:19,424 --> 00:18:20,641
You fool!

346
00:18:21,024 --> 00:18:23,136
Do you even know what you're saying?

347
00:18:23,424 --> 00:18:24,928
I have nothing more to say.

348
00:18:26,880 --> 00:18:27,731
You fool!

349
00:18:27,731 --> 00:18:28,732
Where are you going?

350
00:18:28,896 --> 00:18:29,858
Sit back down!

351
00:18:41,870 --> 00:18:42,752
Goodbye.

352
00:18:47,232 --> 00:18:48,127
Haneul.

353
00:18:49,792 --> 00:18:51,264
Why do you work at a coffee shop?

354
00:18:52,128 --> 00:18:53,504
You used to be a tutor, right?

355
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:56,160
Yeah.

356
00:18:57,184 --> 00:18:58,846
But I don't remember
how to teach at all.

357
00:18:59,776 --> 00:19:01,598
I'm not fit to teach right now.

358
00:19:02,349 --> 00:19:03,767
You might remember as you teach.

359
00:19:05,018 --> 00:19:07,980
But that would just
waste the students' money.

360
00:19:09,248 --> 00:19:10,149
You're a good guy.

361
00:19:11,200 --> 00:19:12,640
I'm a sincere person.

362
00:19:14,272 --> 00:19:15,946
Then why do you work here?

363
00:19:18,073 --> 00:19:19,074
To see Haneul.

364
00:19:20,409 --> 00:19:21,160
There you go.

365
00:19:22,944 --> 00:19:24,224
I'm serious.

366
00:19:26,368 --> 00:19:27,332
It doesn't work.

367
00:19:28,667 --> 00:19:30,816
That's not how it works.

368
00:19:33,297 --> 00:19:34,506
Then how?

369
00:19:39,360 --> 00:19:40,387
Like this.

370
00:19:41,054 --> 00:19:42,139
The way I take care of you.

371
00:19:45,312 --> 00:19:46,685
Huh! Spider!

372
00:19:47,552 --> 00:19:48,437
Liar.

373
00:19:48,437 --> 00:19:49,730
I'm serious.

374
00:19:50,272 --> 00:19:51,231
Let me get it off.

375
00:19:51,936 --> 00:19:52,649
Is it gone?

376
00:20:12,480 --> 00:20:13,056
Haneul.

377
00:20:13,056 --> 00:20:13,632
Ah.

378
00:20:14,208 --> 00:20:15,104
Yeo Saebyeok.

379
00:20:17,152 --> 00:20:19,134
Are you done? Let's go.

380
00:20:19,424 --> 00:20:20,176
Ah?

381
00:20:20,832 --> 00:20:21,504
Yeo Saebyeok.

382
00:20:22,912 --> 00:20:23,847
I'm your fan.

383
00:20:25,376 --> 00:20:26,057
Thanks.

384
00:20:26,528 --> 00:20:27,726
Change and let's go.

385
00:20:31,328 --> 00:20:32,189
Wait a moment.

386
00:20:41,823 --> 00:20:44,451
Haneul forgot you, right?

387
00:20:47,008 --> 00:20:48,121
You must be really sad.

388
00:20:48,121 --> 00:20:49,289
It seems like

389
00:20:51,904 --> 00:20:52,992
none of your business.

390
00:20:52,992 --> 00:20:54,688
How is it not my business?

391
00:20:55,616 --> 00:20:56,964
Haneul and I

392
00:20:57,760 --> 00:20:59,049
are pretty close.

393
00:21:03,104 --> 00:21:04,012
Let's go.

394
00:21:05,792 --> 00:21:07,766
- See you tomorrow, Haneul.
- See you tomorrow.

395
00:21:19,403 --> 00:21:21,863
What's wrong?

396
00:21:26,048 --> 00:21:26,952
Don't

397
00:21:26,952 --> 00:21:27,828
be with others...

398
00:21:35,008 --> 00:21:36,295
Be careful around guys.

399
00:21:37,376 --> 00:21:38,672
You're the most dangerous one.

400
00:21:45,216 --> 00:21:46,013
So,

401
00:21:46,528 --> 00:21:47,681
who made a mistake?

402
00:21:48,224 --> 00:21:49,850
Come on. Tell me.

403
00:21:52,032 --> 00:21:52,852
I made a mistake.

404
00:21:55,904 --> 00:21:58,976
God, please forgive
the sins of this Satan.

405
00:22:02,654 --> 00:22:04,364
Amen.

406
00:22:18,528 --> 00:22:20,864
Mom, I'm home.

407
00:22:22,799 --> 00:22:24,593
Home is the most comfortable place.

408
00:22:25,802 --> 00:22:29,152
But someone used to complain
about being uncomfortable at home.

409
00:22:31,266 --> 00:22:32,576
Is there someone ungrateful?

410
00:22:34,144 --> 00:22:35,968
There's one lying
right there on the sofa.

411
00:22:39,872 --> 00:22:41,234
Did you two fight again?

412
00:22:42,752 --> 00:22:44,029
Do we fight often?

413
00:22:44,064 --> 00:22:45,614
You always come home after a fight.

414
00:22:48,608 --> 00:22:49,659
Was I like that before?

415
00:22:54,816 --> 00:22:55,584
Are you tired?

416
00:22:57,280 --> 00:22:58,377
No.

417
00:23:02,592 --> 00:23:03,488
Mm-hmm.

418
00:23:07,008 --> 00:23:08,345
It's just that even now,

419
00:23:09,088 --> 00:23:11,040
I can't believe
I'm already 29 years old.

420
00:23:13,024 --> 00:23:16,103
Whether you're 29 or 19,
there's no difference.

421
00:23:16,384 --> 00:23:18,480
You've always been
doing what you want to do.

422
00:23:22,080 --> 00:23:24,027
When I couldn't play tennis anymore,

423
00:23:24,384 --> 00:23:26,029
was I doing okay?

424
00:23:26,029 --> 00:23:27,989
Of course not.

425
00:23:28,512 --> 00:23:30,367
You were practically a little devil.

426
00:23:33,024 --> 00:23:33,870
Really?

427
00:23:35,372 --> 00:23:36,416
Of course.

428
00:23:37,152 --> 00:23:40,210
Losing your dream
overnight is a huge deal.

429
00:23:41,408 --> 00:23:45,549
For a while, you locked yourself away
and didn't talk to anyone in the family.

430
00:23:46,716 --> 00:23:48,301
We were really worried about you.

431
00:23:50,512 --> 00:23:51,263
But

432
00:23:51,972 --> 00:23:53,056
how did I get through it?

433
00:23:59,062 --> 00:24:02,304
One day, Saebyeok came to us.

434
00:24:03,072 --> 00:24:05,026
He asked us to trust him.

435
00:24:05,694 --> 00:24:09,030
He said he could help you.

436
00:24:10,740 --> 00:24:12,117
So we gave him a chance.

437
00:24:16,329 --> 00:24:17,581
What did he do?

438
00:24:18,582 --> 00:24:21,918
He opened your room and went in.

439
00:24:22,794 --> 00:24:25,755
Sometimes he stayed for an hour,

440
00:24:26,298 --> 00:24:27,883
or 30 minutes,

441
00:24:28,383 --> 00:24:30,010
or even the whole day.

442
00:24:30,752 --> 00:24:32,429
He came every day.

443
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:36,516
One day, Saebyeok stopped coming.

444
00:24:38,226 --> 00:24:39,811
And then you came out on your own.

445
00:24:53,376 --> 00:24:55,535
Hey, aren't you leaving yet?

446
00:24:56,480 --> 00:24:58,560
You've finished dinner here.
Time to leave.

447
00:25:00,224 --> 00:25:02,528
- I'm sleeping here tonight.
- There's no room for you.

448
00:25:02,528 --> 00:25:03,840
I'll sleep with Mom.

449
00:25:06,463 --> 00:25:09,299
By the way, Mom,
how are Saebyeok's parents doing?

450
00:25:11,051 --> 00:25:13,595
Of course, they're doing great.

451
00:25:15,680 --> 00:25:19,100
Oh dear, I almost forgot.
Today is garbage disposal day.

452
00:25:19,392 --> 00:25:20,704
Haneul, you take out the trash.

453
00:25:21,686 --> 00:25:22,229
No.

454
00:25:23,008 --> 00:25:25,152
- Make Gi Saetbyeol do it.
- Hey, you.

455
00:25:25,152 --> 00:25:26,983
(Dummy: One message)

456
00:25:30,752 --> 00:25:31,863
(Garbage sorting)

457
00:25:44,064 --> 00:25:45,502
What are you doing?

458
00:25:47,796 --> 00:25:48,838
Correcting a mistake.

459
00:25:51,216 --> 00:25:52,968
Did you get this back again?

460
00:26:05,056 --> 00:26:05,688
It was me.

461
00:26:06,848 --> 00:26:07,840
I got it back.

462
00:26:09,536 --> 00:26:10,569
I must be crazy.

463
00:26:11,808 --> 00:26:12,737
It's too embarrassing.

464
00:26:14,176 --> 00:26:15,104
What's embarrassing?

465
00:26:15,744 --> 00:26:16,768
What are you doing here?

466
00:26:16,768 --> 00:26:18,528
Going to my mother-in-law's
to show respect.

467
00:26:18,560 --> 00:26:19,424
You're crazy.

468
00:26:19,616 --> 00:26:20,704
Who's your mother-in-law?

469
00:26:20,704 --> 00:26:21,913
Ms. Kim Myeongsook.

470
00:26:22,816 --> 00:26:23,498
Get lost.

471
00:26:25,292 --> 00:26:26,251
What's embarrassing?

472
00:26:30,368 --> 00:26:31,214
What?

473
00:26:32,128 --> 00:26:33,133
I said "value".
[*"Value" sounds similar to "embarrassing" in Korean]

474
00:26:34,467 --> 00:26:36,448
I was thinking of the value
of this trash can.

475
00:26:37,408 --> 00:26:38,513
You're crazy too.

476
00:26:38,513 --> 00:26:39,472
Hey, you.

477
00:26:39,872 --> 00:26:40,724
Anything else?

478
00:26:41,856 --> 00:26:42,976
If not, take a walk with me.

479
00:26:44,192 --> 00:26:44,894
No.

480
00:26:45,472 --> 00:26:46,396
Why should I?

481
00:26:47,772 --> 00:26:50,848
(Lumen English School)

482
00:26:54,592 --> 00:26:56,489
It's bringing back painful memories.

483
00:26:57,024 --> 00:26:58,908
I always got hit for not doing homework.

484
00:26:59,488 --> 00:27:00,827
I wonder how the director is.

485
00:27:02,208 --> 00:27:03,776
His son runs it now.

486
00:27:06,752 --> 00:27:07,584
Family business.

487
00:27:14,382 --> 00:27:16,926
Ah! The tteokbokki store here is gone.

488
00:27:17,568 --> 00:27:19,638
We came here together
on its last day of business.

489
00:27:20,448 --> 00:27:23,350
I really want some. It was so good.

490
00:27:33,824 --> 00:27:36,384
(Saelun Obstetrics and Gynecology)
This is where my bond with you started.

491
00:27:37,920 --> 00:27:38,720
What bond?

492
00:27:39,908 --> 00:27:40,672
It's destiny.

493
00:27:43,584 --> 00:27:44,579
Bad feng shui here.

494
00:27:59,616 --> 00:28:00,720
It's closed.

495
00:28:02,432 --> 00:28:03,098
Let's go in.

496
00:28:04,480 --> 00:28:05,809
Didn't you hear what I said?

497
00:28:06,400 --> 00:28:07,776
It's closed.

498
00:28:12,032 --> 00:28:13,316
We can just climb over.

499
00:28:15,744 --> 00:28:16,903
Is this right?

500
00:28:18,571 --> 00:28:19,712
What if we get caught?

501
00:28:19,712 --> 00:28:20,740
That won't happen.

502
00:28:20,832 --> 00:28:22,158
How do you know?

503
00:28:22,867 --> 00:28:23,743
I've done it before.

504
00:28:27,414 --> 00:28:28,748
It won't be in the news, will it?

505
00:28:29,376 --> 00:28:32,502
Actor A climbed a wall
and trespassed at his alma mater.

506
00:28:33,248 --> 00:28:34,713
It can make the school famous.

507
00:28:49,602 --> 00:28:50,854
Ask whatever you want to ask.

508
00:28:56,608 --> 00:28:58,153
What did you do in my room?

509
00:28:58,880 --> 00:28:59,570
Room?

510
00:29:02,198 --> 00:29:03,074
You came every day.

511
00:29:04,826 --> 00:29:06,048
What did we do?

512
00:29:08,121 --> 00:29:08,913
I hit you.

513
00:29:09,312 --> 00:29:10,272
Lunatic!

514
00:29:10,665 --> 00:29:12,288
Why did you hit me?

515
00:29:13,418 --> 00:29:14,272
Exactly.

516
00:29:14,627 --> 00:29:15,936
I had no reason to hit you.

517
00:29:16,254 --> 00:29:16,963
So I let you off.

518
00:29:17,005 --> 00:29:18,144
Hey, stop joking around.

519
00:29:23,904 --> 00:29:25,696
We just watched dramas

520
00:29:25,984 --> 00:29:27,223
and movies.

521
00:29:27,584 --> 00:29:28,975
Why watched them?

522
00:29:30,112 --> 00:29:32,854
I wanted you
to see stories that suit you.

523
00:29:34,080 --> 00:29:36,566
There are different people in the world,

524
00:29:37,504 --> 00:29:39,819
each facing their own trials

525
00:29:40,278 --> 00:29:42,614
and fighting back in their own ways.

526
00:29:42,912 --> 00:29:45,116
They overcome trials and move on.

527
00:29:46,464 --> 00:29:48,161
You're one of those stories.

528
00:29:52,448 --> 00:29:54,000
So I think

529
00:29:54,144 --> 00:29:57,295
you can rewrite your story too.

530
00:30:04,544 --> 00:30:06,763
But how did you suddenly become a star?

531
00:30:09,408 --> 00:30:11,059
You watched them so intently.

532
00:30:11,776 --> 00:30:12,928
I wanted you to see me too.

533
00:30:14,771 --> 00:30:15,980
Did it happen?

534
00:30:16,189 --> 00:30:17,857
Thinking of you made it happen.

535
00:30:19,275 --> 00:30:20,109
Is that so?

536
00:30:22,496 --> 00:30:24,531
Then give me half your acting fees.

537
00:30:25,248 --> 00:30:25,824
Okay.

538
00:30:26,848 --> 00:30:27,872
It's all yours.

539
00:30:33,665 --> 00:30:34,720
We...

540
00:30:36,800 --> 00:30:38,461
Why were we together
just for seven years?

541
00:30:42,656 --> 00:30:44,467
Because you dumped me for three years.

542
00:30:45,056 --> 00:30:46,427
Didn't you give up even then?

543
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:49,180
You know how I am.

544
00:30:52,800 --> 00:30:56,062
Didn't you like anyone else
in those three years?

545
00:30:56,384 --> 00:30:58,481
I'm just the type to love only one.

546
00:31:00,576 --> 00:31:01,734
That's true.

547
00:31:02,528 --> 00:31:05,113
You even use one thing for a long time.

548
00:31:05,728 --> 00:31:06,656
So,

549
00:31:07,008 --> 00:31:08,157
I'll be with you

550
00:31:08,157 --> 00:31:09,659
for a long time.

551
00:31:09,920 --> 00:31:10,827
I refuse.

552
00:31:11,040 --> 00:31:11,953
I'm willing.

553
00:31:11,953 --> 00:31:12,996
You're mine.

554
00:31:14,208 --> 00:31:15,665
Where did you learn to sweet-talk?

555
00:31:16,224 --> 00:31:17,125
I absolutely

556
00:31:17,504 --> 00:31:18,710
won't break up with you.

557
00:31:21,664 --> 00:31:23,296
It's not that
you won't break up with me.

558
00:31:23,872 --> 00:31:25,120
You just won't accept it.

559
00:31:26,336 --> 00:31:27,343
What's the difference?

560
00:31:27,844 --> 00:31:29,053
Don't ask so calmly.

561
00:31:29,856 --> 00:31:30,471
It's scary.

562
00:31:31,488 --> 00:31:33,504
Romance is scary by nature.

563
00:31:36,160 --> 00:31:37,061
Let's go home.

564
00:31:39,872 --> 00:31:40,899
Can we hold hands?

565
00:31:42,432 --> 00:31:43,985
If we do, I won't go to your place.

566
00:31:44,768 --> 00:31:45,612
That's harsh.

567
00:31:46,560 --> 00:31:47,488
I'll say it again.

568
00:31:48,256 --> 00:31:50,408
You and I aren't in a relationship now.

569
00:31:51,520 --> 00:31:52,702
That's harsh too.

570
00:31:53,696 --> 00:31:55,246
People should know their place.

571
00:31:56,832 --> 00:31:58,207
You've always been harsh with me.

572
00:32:00,032 --> 00:32:01,669
Have you always been gentle with me?

573
00:33:03,584 --> 00:33:04,630
Yeo Saebyeok.

574
00:33:07,392 --> 00:33:08,160
Yeo Saebyeok.

575
00:33:15,410 --> 00:33:16,224
Yeo Saebyeok.

576
00:33:35,584 --> 00:33:36,597
I'm sorry.

577
00:33:43,438 --> 00:33:44,288
Forgive me.

578
00:34:06,074 --> 00:34:09,280
♪The more I try to run away♪

579
00:34:09,280 --> 00:34:11,092
♪The clearer it becomes♪

580
00:34:12,608 --> 00:34:15,984
♪Even the word "love"♪

581
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:17,471
♪Can't convey how I feel♪

582
00:34:19,360 --> 00:34:22,613
♪Watching your shadow moving forward♪

583
00:34:22,613 --> 00:34:24,474
♪Sometimes, I resent you♪

584
00:34:24,474 --> 00:34:26,272
♪But without you,
everything feels strange♪

585
00:34:26,272 --> 00:34:31,635
♪The pain also makes me grow♪

586
00:34:33,082 --> 00:34:34,982
♪There is a lot to say♪

587
00:34:34,982 --> 00:34:36,402
♪Trying to separate us♪

588
00:34:36,715 --> 00:34:39,560
♪Even if I look like a fool♪

589
00:34:40,156 --> 00:34:41,676
♪It doesn't matter♪

590
00:34:41,676 --> 00:34:43,642
♪This is how we are♪

591
00:34:43,642 --> 00:34:46,557
♪Connected to each other♪

592
00:34:46,618 --> 00:34:50,400
♪We are truly strange♪

593
00:34:50,400 --> 00:34:53,669
♪Pushing each other away,
yet embracing again♪

594
00:34:53,669 --> 00:34:55,962
♪Between love and pain♪

595
00:34:55,994 --> 00:34:59,005
♪In some corner♪

596
00:34:59,005 --> 00:35:02,784
♪In the end, we can only be together♪

597
00:35:09,748 --> 00:35:13,580
♪Because that's us♪

598
00:35:16,992 --> 00:35:18,394
♪Even if what we said yesterday♪

599
00:35:18,394 --> 00:35:19,848
♪Remains in the heart♪

600
00:35:20,026 --> 00:35:21,818
♪As time passes♪

601
00:35:21,818 --> 00:35:23,034
♪Maybe I'll laugh about it♪

602
00:35:23,034 --> 00:35:25,114
♪Even those painful memories♪

603
00:35:25,114 --> 00:35:26,234
♪Are also ours♪

604
00:35:26,388 --> 00:35:28,968
♪Seems we can♪

605
00:35:28,968 --> 00:35:31,136
♪Be more understanding♪

606
00:35:31,136 --> 00:35:33,564
♪I clearly told myself♪

607
00:35:34,586 --> 00:35:36,672
♪Never to see you again♪

608
00:35:37,082 --> 00:35:39,791
♪But hearing your voice♪

609
00:35:40,148 --> 00:35:41,408
♪I completely break down♪
